Ian Wood and Sean Peacock

We have created a simple scene with a car driving in circles around a flag.
You can change the camera to look at the interior of the car, which has a piston.

1. Both the car and the bird follow a spline path.
2. The car and bird also use quaternions and SLERPing to rotate on their path.
3. The flag uses shape deformation to creat the wave effect.
4. The flag also uses bones for its deformation.
5. The piston uses hierarchical modeling and inverse kinematics.
6. The particles have velocity and experience elastic collisions with each other and the walls/piston.
7. We use particles with the piston.
8. We don't have obstacle avoidance.

Additional Instructions:
Press "c" to swap between the 2 cameras.

We struggled to get the piston to work. It has a lot of moving parts,
and we were not using the angles from our inverse kinematics function properly at first.

Sean was responsible for all of the object creating, the spline following, and the quaternions.
Ian was responsible for the flag shape deformation with bones, the lighting, and the particles.
We worked collaboratively on all of the drawing of the objects, as well as the creation of the piston.

We did not use AI or resources outside of class materials.